com.inqwell.any.server

Class LocalTransaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractAny
      • com.inqwell.any.AbstractTransaction
        • com.inqwell.any.server.TwoPhaseTransaction
          • com.inqwell.any.server.LocalTransaction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, Transaction, Serializable, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PrimaryTransaction, RemoteTransaction

    public abstract class LocalTransaction
extends TwoPhaseTransaction
implements Transaction, Cloneable
    Base class for a transaction with a two-phase commit policy in a local Inq environment.
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.6 $
    Author:
    $Author: sanderst $

      • acquireResource

        public Any acquireResource(Any spec,
                           ResourceAllocator allocator,
                           long timeout)
                    throws AnyException
        Description copied from interface: Transaction
        Acquire the specified resource from the given allocator. The implementation may return the same resource more than once for a given specification and allocator during the lifetime of the transaction.

        If there are no resources available then the allocator determines the policy of either waiting or throwing. The timeout argument may be used by the allocator.

        The transaction implementation is responsible for releasing any resources this method returns on commit or abort.

        Specified by:
        acquireResource in interface Transaction
        Overrides:
        acquireResource in class AbstractTransaction
        Returns:
        the resource
        Throws:
        AnyException

      • getPhase1Objects

        protected Map getPhase1Objects()
        Description copied from class: TwoPhaseTransaction
        Returns the Map of phase 1 objects. This will either be the participants or the set of objects that are added to the transaction during a call to a mutator. In the latter case, once called the alternate set is also cleared, so this method can only be called by subclasses when they wish to perform final processing on this set. For continued access to whichever set is in effect call getActiveObjects().
        Specified by:
        getPhase1Objects in class TwoPhaseTransaction
